<TITLE> Major rivers overflow to worsen flood </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 23 (bdnews24.com) Torrential rain in the past few days and onrush of hill waters saw most of the major rivers swell, flooding large swathes of the country. Flood Forecasts and Warning Centre (FFWC) Monday said at least five rivers at seven points were flowing above the danger level, giving rise to flooding in parts of the country. Though Sunday ushered in moderate to heavy rainfalls all over the country, Monday morning in Dhaka seemed to be basking under a welcome sun. The skies remained clear until midday, though the met office said most areas in the country might have rains. Temperature during the day might remain unchanged. The FFWC said the river Padma was flowing 1 cm above the danger mark at Goalando point, the Surma was flowing 7 cm above the danger level at Kanaighat and 9 cm at Sunamganj. Someshwari was 19 cm above the danger mark at Durgapur, Gomti 135 cm at Comilla point and 176 cm at Devidwar, and Muhuri was flowing 39 cm above the danger level at Parshuram point. Weatherman Golam Mostafa told bdnews24.com until 6pm Monday, some areas in Dhaka, Khulna, Barisal and Chittagong divisions might have heavy rainfall. The sun sets in Dhaka at 6:46 pm Monday and rises Tuesday at 5:24 am. bdnew
